, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1325–Bef February 1360/1361":"about 1325–before February 1360","1325–1360":"1325–1360","1337–1388":"1337–1388","1335–1360":"1335–1360","1315–1394":"1315–1394","1290–1351":"1290–1351","Abt 1351":"about 1351","Bef February 1360/1361":"before February 1360","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","1325":"1325","1335":"1335","1388":"1388","Abt 1325":"about 1325","1351":"1351","1394":"1394","1360":"1360","1290":"1290","Of, Strathbogie, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Huntly, Aberdeenshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Otterburn, Northumberland, England":"Otterburn, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Gordon","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from Gordon in Berwickshire, named with Welsh <i>gor</i> ‘spacious’ + <i>din</i> ‘fort’.","English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Gourdon in Saône-et-Loire, so called from the Gallo-Roman personal name <i>Gordus</i> + the locative suffix <i>-o</i>, <i>-ōnis</i>.","English (of Norman origin): alternatively, said to be a nickname from a diminutive of Old French <i>gourd</i> ‘heavy, dull, sluggish’ (compare 8 below)."],"variants":[{"name":"Gordin","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Eyal, Moisey, Yakov, Zalman, Erez, Faina, Haya, Mendel.  Russian Leonid, Aleksandr, Boris, Feiga, Genady.","Jewish (from Russia): variant of   Gordon   5.","French: variant of   Gourdin  . This surname is very rare in France."]},{"name":"Gordan","meanings":["German: variant of   Jordan  . The surname <i>Gordan</i> is very rare in Germany.","Irish (Wexford and Sligo): adopted as an Anglicized form of <b>Mag Mhuirneacháin</b> ‘son of <i>Muirneachán</i>’, a personal name from a diminutive of <i>muirneach</i> ‘lovable’."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Gordon was born about 1325, in Huntly, Aberdeenshire, Scotland, United Kingdom as the son of Adam Gordon 8th Laird of Gordon. He married Elizabeth. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died before February 1360, in Otterburn, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1325–Bef February 1360/1361":"umbes 1325–enne veebruari 1360","1325–1360":"1325–1360","1337–1388":"1337–1388","1335–1360":"1335–1360","1315–1394":"1315–1394","1290–1351":"1290–1351","Abt 1351":"umbes 1351","Bef February 1360/1361":"enne veebruari 1360","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","1325":"1325","1335":"1335","1388":"1388","Abt 1325":"umbes 1325","1351":"1351","1394":"1394","1360":"1360","1290":"1290","Of, Strathbogie, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Huntly, Aberdeenshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Otterburn, Northumberland, England":"Otterburn, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1325–Bef February 1360/1361":"noin 1325–ennen vuotta helmikuu 1360","1325–1360":"1325–1360","1337–1388":"1337–1388","1335–1360":"1335–1360","1315–1394":"1315–1394","1290–1351":"1290–1351","Abt 1351":"noin 1351","Bef February 1360/1361":"ennen vuotta helmikuu 1360","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","1325":"1325","1335":"1335","1388":"1388","Abt 1325":"noin 1325","1351":"1351","1394":"1394","1360":"1360","1290":"1290","Of, Strathbogie, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Huntly, Aberdeenshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Otterburn, Northumberland, England":"Otterburn, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1325–Bef February 1360/1361":"environ 1325–avant février 1360","1325–1360":"1325–1360","1337–1388":"1337–1388","1335–1360":"1335–1360","1315–1394":"1315–1394","1290–1351":"1290–1351","Abt 1351":"environ 1351","Bef February 1360/1361":"avant février 1360","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","1325":"1325","1335":"1335","1388":"1388"